Tropical Smoothie Café, LLC (“TSC”, “we”, “us” or “our”) is committed to protecting the privacy of customers and users of our Services (as defined below).
This Privacy Policy applies to information that identifies or relates to users of our Services (“Personal Information”) that TSC collects when users interact with us through our Services and in our corporate owned and operated restaurant located at 1155 Mount Vernon Hwy Unit #1040, Atlanta, GA 30338. This includes information collected through our website and mobile application (including our Tropical Smoothie Cafe App), Tropical Smoothie Cafe branded social networking services, direct marketing campaigns, and when you purchase our products, subscribe to our news, and offers, enter one of our promotions or contact customer support (collectively, our “Services”).
By accessing or using any of our Services or providing us with your Personal Information, you agree to our processing and handling of your Personal Information in accordance with this Privacy Policy. If you are a resident of California or Virginia, you may have additional rights as set forth in Section 9 below.
With the exception of our one corporate owned and operated restaurant in Atlanta, Georgia, Tropical Smoothie Cafe restaurants are independently owned and operated by franchisees. We ask our franchisees to abide by our privacy practices, but each franchisee is independently responsible for its legal compliance, regulatory compliance, and related data practices for any data that they may collect.
1. 	Types of Information We Collect and How It Is Used
TSC gathers Personal Information, such as first and last name, address, email address, zip code, mobile number, favorite Tropical Smoothie Cafe location, and birthdate, when voluntarily submitted by you while using our Services.  We also track the transactions you make, including where and when you make them, in connection with our Tropic Rewards® loyalty program (“Tropic Rewards”).
For example, Personal Information may be collected from you to:
Provide, develop, and improve the Services;
Receive your feedback on our Services and our products;
Send you marketing communications based on your interests and preferences;
Follow up with you on certain promotions and limited time offerings;
Enter you in one of our contests or sweepstakes;
Inform you about our brand or events;
Maintain records for administrative purposes;
Protect customer security;
Detect and prevent fraud; and
Comply with any law, legal process, or law enforcement request.
We also offer various Services that are provided through third parties. For example, our online ordering is provided by Olo. Olo will provide us and/or our franchisees information relating to your order so that it can be prepared for delivery or pickup – this includes the items ordered and the location and time of pickup.
If you apply for a position at the Tropical Smoothie Cafe support center, our one corporate owned and operated restaurant or one of our franchisee owned and operated restaurants, we collect the name, address, phone number, email address, employment information, and educational information you submit. We or our franchisees, as applicable, use this information for processing job applications and hiring purposes.  Please note that we only hire and employ applicants for the Tropical Smoothie Cafe support center and our one corporate owned and operated restaurant located at 1155 Mt. Vernon Highway, Unit #1040, Atlanta, Georgia 30338.  If you are applying for a position at a franchised restaurant, your information will be sent directly to the franchise owner who is responsible for their own hiring and employment-related policies and decisions.
If a customer signs up to receive Tropical Smoothie Cafe emails or creates a Tropic Rewards account, the customer is opting in to receive email communications from Tropical Smoothie Cafe. The customer may opt out of receiving email communications from Tropical Smoothie Cafe by clicking on the unsubscribe link at the bottom of one of our email communications or
clicking here
.
We also collect certain information automatically through the use of cookies and other tracking technologies.
2.
Disclosure of Personal Information
TSC may disclose Personal Information with affiliated companies that we own or control, as well as our independent franchisees, in connection with providing you Services. We ask any affiliated companies and independent franchisees to comply with our Privacy Policy, but such affiliated companies and independent franchisees are responsible for their compliance with applicable laws and regulations.
We may also disclose Personal Information with service providers engaged by us to perform a variety of functions, such as fulfilling orders, assisting with promotions, conducting background checks, and providing technical support for our Services ("service providers”). These service providers may have access to Personal Information if needed to perform such functions. However, these service providers may only use such Personal Information to perform that function and may not use it for any other purpose.
We may also disclose the Personal Information we collect to our analytics vendors and partners to develop aggregate analysis and business intelligence for our advertising and marketing purposes. For example, we use Personal Information to create custom audiences and measure the success of promotions.
We also disclose Personal Information to social media platforms and third-party advertising platforms for purposes of targeted advertising of promotions, products, and services we think may be of interest to you. In certain states, you can request that we stop such targeted advertising as noted in Section 9 below.
TSC reserves the right to use or disclose any Personal Information as needed to satisfy any law, regulation, legal request, or legal process, to exercise or defend legal claims, to protect the integrity of our Services, to prevent fraud, to protect the security of our systems and facilities, to fulfill your requests, or to cooperate in any law enforcement investigation or an investigation on a matter of public safety.
We may disclose your Personal Information to a third-party that acquires TSC or our assets as part of a sale, merger, reorganization or bankruptcy, or other proceeding.
