9.
State Specific Notices
A. Additional Notice for California Consumers
Tropical Smoothie Cafe is mindful of our responsibilities under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA as amended by the California Privacy Rights Act (collectively,
California Privacy Laws)). This portion of our Privacy Policy applies to California Consumers within the meaning of the California Privacy Laws.
a. Notice at Collection
We collect information from users as described in our Privacy Policy. The “Personal Information,” as defined in California Civil Code § 1798.140(o), we collect includes:
Identifiers such as name, postal and email addresses, internet protocol (IP) address, unique personal identifier, online identifier and token identifier when you submit your information to create an account with us, join Tropic Rewards, interact with us on social media, or sign up to learn more about our products and services.
The following categories of protected classification characteristics under California or federal law: birthdate when you sign up to receive special offers as part of Tropic Rewards.
Commercial information such as records of products or services purchased, or obtained, or considered from us.
Internet or other similar network activity information, including, but not limited to, browsing history on our websites, search history, information on your interaction with our websites or applications.
Geolocation data such as physical location or movements.
Inferences drawn from other Personal Information, such as profiles reflecting consumer preferences.
Sensitive Personal Information in the form of precise geolocation but only if you turn on location services in your Tropical Smoothie Cafe App.
We collect this Personal Information so that we can provide you Services, get your feedback, share promotions, enter you into contests, inform you about our brand, send you marketing communications, personalize your interaction, and maintain records. We do not sell this Personal Information to third parties but may disclose it to affiliated companies that we own or control, as well our independent franchisees. We may also disclose Personal Information with service providers engaged by us to perform a variety of functions, such as fulfilling orders, assisting with promotions, providing technical services for our websites, etc.
We generally retain your Personal Information for as long as you have an account or as long as required to comply with legal requirements or fulfill the purpose of the collection.
b. How We Collect, Use, and Share Personal Information
(i)
Personal Information Collected on California Consumers in the Last Twelve Months
We collect information from users as described in our Privacy Policy. The “Personal Information,” as defined in California Civil Code § 1798.140(o), we have obtained on California residents within the last twelve months includes:
Identifiers such as name, postal and email addresses, IP address, unique personal identifier, online identifier and token identifier when you submit your information to create an account with us, join Tropic Rewards, interact with us on social media, or sign up to learn more about our products and services.
The following categories of protected classification characteristics under California or federal law: birthdate when you sign up to receive special offers as part of Tropic Rewards.
Commercial information such as records of products or services purchased, or obtained, or considered from us.
Internet or other similar network activity information, including, but not limited to, browsing history on our websites, search history, information on your interaction with our websites or applications.
Geolocation data such as physical location or movements.
Inferences drawn from other Personal Information, such as profiles reflecting consumer preferences.
Sensitive Personal Information in the form of precise geolocation if you have allowed such tracking.
Please note that Personal Information does not include publicly available information from government records or made publicly available by you such as on social media sites, de-identified or aggregate consumer information, and Personal Information protected by certain other sector-specific federal or California statutes.
(ii)
Our Use of Personal Information for Business or Commercial Purposes in the Last Twelve Months
For each of the above categories, we use the Personal Information we collect for the commercial and business purposes disclosed in this Privacy Policy. These commercial and business purposes include:
Providing, developing and improving our Services;
Personalizing our Services to you;
Audits and reporting relating to particular transactions and interactions, including online interactions, you may have with us or others on our behalf;
Detecting and protecting against security incidents, and malicious, deceptive, fraudulent or illegal activity, and prosecuting the same;
